======================================================================
PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS
Minimal Framework for Six Remainder Domains
======================================================================

QUESTION: What is the minimal description?

From Phase 1: six domains, all with integer + remainder structure.
From Phase 2: 4 confirmed connections, 1 partial, 1 null.
The data supports outcome (b): PARTIAL COLLAPSE.

======================================================================
THE THREE SUBGROUPS
======================================================================

SUBGROUP A: Phase-Periodic Domains
--------------------------------------------------

  Members: {Theta vacuum, Bohr-Sommerfeld, Berry phase, Brillouin zone}

  Shared structure:
    Energy: E(φ) = A - B cos(φ)
    Phase variable: φ ∈ [0, 8R₂)
    Period: 8R₂ × (domain scale)
    Minimum: φ = 0 (remainder = 0)
    Maximum: φ = 4R₂ (half-period)
    Integer: counts complete phase cycles (winding number)
    Remainder: fractional phase (the observable)

  Unified form verification:

    Theta vacuum         scale = 1      period = 8R₂ × 1
    Bohr-Sommerfeld      scale = ℏ      period = 8R₂ × ℏ
    Berry phase          scale = 1      period = 8R₂ × 1
    Brillouin zone       scale = 1/a    period = 8R₂ × 1/a

  Key identities (all EXACT):
    Full period:  2π = 8R₂  (True)
    Half period:  π  = 4R₂  (True)
    Quarter:      π/2 = 2R₂ (True)

  Ground state principle:
    On an 8R₂-periodic domain with energy E = A - B cos(φ),
    the minimum is at φ = 0 (remainder = 0).
    This is why θ_QCD = 0 (PHYS-7).
    This is why the BZ band minimum is at k = 0.
    This is why the Maslov ground state has n = 0.

  Internal connections (Phase 2):
    Q1: Maslov correction = Berry phase / (8R₂)  [tautological]
    Q6: Theta E(θ) and BZ E(k) are same cosine   [structural]
    These connections are INTERNAL to Subgroup A.


SUBGROUP B: Monotonic Accumulation
--------------------------------------------------

  Members: {RG running}

  Structure:
    Coupling: α⁻¹(μ) = α⁻¹(μ₀) + Σ_f [Q²/(12R₂)] × ln(μ/m_f) × Θ(μ-m_f)
    Variable: ln(μ) (logarithmic energy)
    Step size: Q²/(12R₂) per flavor (contains R₂)
    Boundaries: at μ = m_f (mass thresholds, measured)
    NOT periodic: thresholds at unequal intervals
    Integer analog: number of active flavors
    Remainder analog: accumulated running between thresholds

  Step size 1/(3π) = 1/(12R₂): True (EXACT)

  Why Subgroup B is separate from A:
    - No periodicity (VP running is monotonic)
    - Thresholds are measured (not geometric)
    - The energy functional is NOT cosine (it's logarithmic)
    - R₂ appears in step SIZE, not in the period

  Connection to Subgroup A:
    - R₂ is present (in 1/(12R₂), the VP coefficient)
    - There IS a discrete/continuous split (thresholds + running)
    - Phase 2 Q2: structural parallel but not formal equivalence


SUBGROUP C: Topological Quantization
--------------------------------------------------

  Members: {Chern-Simons}

  Structure:
    Invariant: CS(A) mod ℤ
    Modulus: 1 (from large gauge invariance)
    Integer: Chern number c₂ (topological)
    Remainder: fractional CS (gauge-invariant observable)
    Normalization: 1/(8π²) = 1/(256R₄)
    Exponential: exp(2πi·k·CS) = exp(i·8R₂·k·CS)

  Normalization 1/(8π²) = 1/(256R₄): True (EXACT)

  Why Subgroup C is separate:
    - Modulus is 1, not 8R₂ × scale
    - The integer (Chern number) is topological, not phase-counting
    - The CS values for flat connections are pure rationals
    - Transcendental content (R₂, R₄) is in normalization,
      not in the modulus or the CS values themselves

  Connection to Subgroup A:
    - R₂ in the exponential (8R₂ = 2π sets phase periodicity)
    - R₄ in the normalization (256R₄ = 8π² from 4D Chern class)
    - The level k must be integer (like winding number in A)
    - θ_QCD = 0 (Subgroup A) means CS mod ℤ = 0 (Subgroup C)
      — the SAME result expressed in two different frameworks

======================================================================
THE MINIMAL DESCRIPTION
======================================================================

The six domains require THREE structural elements:

  1. ONE geometric constant: R₂ = π/4
     Present in all six domains.
     Sets the phase period (8R₂ = 2π) in Subgroup A.
     Sets the step size (1/(12R₂) = 1/(3π)) in Subgroup B.
     Sets the exponential period (8R₂ = 2π) in Subgroup C.

  2. TWO types of modulus:
     Type I:  8R₂ × scale (phase-periodic, Subgroups A and C exponential)
     Type II: 1 (topological, Subgroup C modulus)
     Subgroup B has no true modulus (monotonic accumulation).

  3. THREE subgroup structures:
     A: Cosine energy on 8R₂-periodic domain, min at R=0
     B: Logarithmic accumulation with R₂-scaled steps
     C: Integer-modular with R₄ normalization from 4D

======================================================================
WHAT COLLAPSES
======================================================================

  COLLAPSES (shared structure across domains):

  (i) R₂ = π/4 is universal.
      Every domain contains R₂. It appears as:
        - The modular period (8R₂ in Subgroup A)
        - The step coefficient (1/(12R₂) in Subgroup B)
        - The exponential period (8R₂ in Subgroup C)
      There is no domain where R₂ is absent.

  (ii) The four Subgroup A domains are ONE structure.
       Theta vacuum, BS, Berry, BZ all satisfy:
         E(φ) = A - B cos(φ), period 8R₂ × scale, min at φ=0
       The Maslov-Berry connection (Q1) and theta-BZ connection (Q6)
       are internal to this single structure.

  (iii) The ground state principle: remainder = 0 at minimum energy.
        This produces θ_QCD = 0 (Subgroup A) and CS mod ℤ = 0 for
        the QCD vacuum (Subgroup C). Same physics, same R = 0.

  DOES NOT COLLAPSE:

  (i) RG running (Subgroup B) is NOT periodic.
      It shares R₂ with the others but the functional form
      is logarithmic, not cosine. The thresholds are measured
      masses, not geometric periods. Phase 2 Q5 returned NULL.

  (ii) CS modulus = 1 is NOT 8R₂ × scale.
       The topological quantization comes from gauge invariance,
       not from phase periodicity. R₂ and R₄ are in the
       normalization and exponential, not in the modulus itself.

======================================================================
SYNTHESIS RESULT: OUTCOME (b) — PARTIAL COLLAPSE
======================================================================

  The six domains collapse to:

  ONE constant: R₂ = π/4 (present in all six)

  TWO modular types:
    Phase-periodic (mod 8R₂ × scale): theta, BS, Berry, BZ
    Topological (mod 1): CS
    Non-periodic (no modulus): RG

  THREE subgroups:
    A = {theta, BS, Berry, BZ}: cosine on 8R₂, min at R=0
    B = {RG}: logarithmic staircase, R₂ in step, no period
    C = {CS}: integer modular, R₄ normalization, R₂ exponential

  ONE principle within Subgroup A:
    Ground state = minimum of -cos(φ) on 8R₂-periodic domain = R=0
    (This is why θ_QCD = 0.)

  R₄ = π²/32 enters when 4D geometry is involved:
    CS normalization (Chern class on 4-manifold)
    Zone boundary energy (standing wave quantization)
    Box energy (boundary condition quantization)

